**cameron_erdos_proved:**

The Cameron-Erdős conjecture is true.

From the lower and upper bounds:
- f(n) ≥ 2^{n/2}
- f(n) ≤ C · 2^{n/2}

We get log₂(f(n)) ∈ [n/2, n/2 + O(1)], which is (1+o(1))·n/2.

**erdos_748_summary:**

Combines all main results:

1. Trivial lower bound: f(n) ≥ 2^{n/2}
2. Green/Sapozhenko upper bound: f(n) ≤ C · 2^{n/2}
3. Precise asymptotic: f(n) ~ c_n · 2^{n/2}

The Cameron-Erdős conjecture is PROVED.
